article_title: French Transport Disrupted After Railway Workers Strike
article_text: SHARE THIS ARTICLE   Share   Tweet   Post   Email  {"contentId":"MOBQ9Z6JTSEW01","position":"brokerboxarticle","dimensions":{"large_desktop":[[120,60]],"small_desktop":[[120,60]],"tablet":[[120,60]]},"strategy":"viewable","positionIncrement":1,"targeting":{"position":"brokerboxarticle1","url":"/news/articles/2013-06-13/french-transport-disrupted-after-railway-workers-strike"},"containerId":"brokerboxarticle-pwj5uzk"}   French train transport was disrupted today after four railroad employees’ unions called a strike to protest a planned reorganization of the service.    Only four out of 10 high-speed and regional trains are running, national rail company SNCF said on its website. The Intercite trains, which provide a non-high-speed long-distance service, are at a third of their normal level, it said. Eurostar, Thalys and trains heading to Germany are not affected, SNCF said.    {"contentId":"MOBQ9Z6JTSEW01","position":"outstream","dimensions":{"large_desktop":[[1,8]],"small_desktop":[[1,8]],"tablet":[[1,8]]},"strategy":"always","type":"Outstream Video Native Ad","targeting":{"position":"outstream","url":"/news/articles/2013-06-13/french-transport-disrupted-after-railway-workers-strike"},"containerId":"outstream-video-1-MOBQ9Z6JTSEW01"}   {"contentId":"MOBQ9Z6JTSEW01","position":"outstream","dimensions":{"mobile":[[1,8]]},"strategy":"always","type":"Outstream Video Native Ad","targeting":{"position":"outstream","url":"/news/articles/2013-06-13/french-transport-disrupted-after-railway-workers-strike"},"containerId":"outstream-video-2-MOBQ9Z6JTSEW01"}   While the metro service in Paris was normal, only one out of three trains serving the region around the capital city was running.    {"contentId":"MOBQ9Z6JTSEW01","position":"box","dimensions":{"mobile":[[300,250],[3,3],[1,1],"fluid"]},"type":"Mobile Body Box Ad","positionIncrement":1,"targeting":{"position":"box1","positionIncrement":1,"url":"/news/articles/2013-06-13/french-transport-disrupted-after-railway-workers-strike"},"containerId":"box-VDA2GWu"}   Participation is “very strong with one out of two rail employees on strike,” Gilbert Garrel, a CGT union representative, was cited as saying by Agence France-Presse.    SNCF spokesman Frank Paul Weber said in an e-mailed message that about 70 percent of on-board ticket collectors, conductors, inspectors and train drivers were on strike.  {"contentId":"MOBQ9Z6JTSEW01","position":"desktop-in-article1","dimensions":{"large_desktop":[[5,4]],"small_desktop":[[5,4]]},"type":"Desktop in article Native Ad","targeting":{"position":"desktop-in-article1","url":"/news/articles/2013-06-13/french-transport-disrupted-after-railway-workers-strike"},"containerId":"desktop-in-article-1-MOBQ9Z6JTSEW01"}   The strike, which began at 7 p.m. last night, is set to continue until 8:00 a.m. tomorrow.  (Updates with details from SNCF in fifth paragraph.)   Published on ‎13‎ ‎June‎, ‎2013‎ ‎12‎:‎33        Have a confidential tip for our reporters?
